transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at SCOREblue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: So, I'm getting billed for a subscription, and I don't need a subscription here,

Speaker 1: and I'm unable to get into my profile and cancel this subscription.

Speaker 2: I must have a card on file. You guys keep sending me SCOREblue stuff.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, sir, these prescriptions have adjustable frequencies,

Speaker 2: so I can see how yours is set up, and we can absolutely get this resolved.

Speaker 1: Could you provide me your full name and date of birth, please?

Speaker 2: Yes. Keith Olsen, O-L-S-E-N, 22264.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I don't know how it's set up, but if we can check that out, it'd be great.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I see this prescription was originally written in October 2025,

Speaker 1: and this was for the 50-milligram Viagra, sildenafil generic.

Speaker 2: Does that sound accurate?

Speaker 1: How much is that a month?

Speaker 2: So, right now, what you are paying for 15 pills is $63.95.

Speaker 1: And how often do I get that?

Speaker 2: Your schedule currently is based on monthly, but this is perfectly adjustable.

Speaker 1: This is not a subscription, so if you wanted to adjust it, we can do that for you.

Speaker 2: Some patients do bimonthly. Some patients do every 3 months.

Speaker 1: Some patients prefer to just put a pause on it,

Speaker 2: and that allows them to call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: So I just had an order shipped, and that would be 15 pills?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it appears that that will probably be here later this week,

Speaker 1: pending the weather circumstance right now.

Speaker 2: Right. Right.

Speaker 1: Oh, that's right. It wasn't shipped there.

Speaker 2: I was tracking it, but it's still en route.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So, I'm trying some of the Rougette, but it's kind of like a gummy.

Speaker 1: It makes my tongue go.

Speaker 2: Yeah. And the Rougette Comparative Ease.

Speaker 1: So we are certified through Pfizer and an FDA-approved company,

Speaker 2: so everything that we sell here is FDA-approved.

Speaker 1: The Rougette, I know a lot of men are trying it,

Speaker 2: but you have to be very careful just because they are not FDA-approved.

Speaker 1: I respect the idea that you're wanting to try it,

Speaker 2: and obviously you're welcome to do so if you want.

Speaker 1: I could just pause your account here,

Speaker 2: and then should you want to return and have access to the remaining refills under the script,

Speaker 1: you could always just give us a call.

Speaker 2: Well, I'll keep the one that's coming.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: I don't remember trying it, though, so I'll keep.

Speaker 1: I've already gotten an order before, or is this my first order?

Speaker 2: No, sir. You've already received an order of this.

Speaker 1: What does it say on the side? Duckies?

Speaker 2: No. It would say Score Blue, and it would say Viagra on it.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Right. And they're 50.

Speaker 2: Correct. Correct.

Speaker 1: I could also adjust your prescription at the same price to 100 milligrams in the future as well,

Speaker 2: if you wanted something a little higher.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: And the same amount of pills doubled the price, right?

Speaker 1: Sir, I would honor your price for 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I might next time do that. I'm not sure.

Speaker 1: I'll try one of the 50s and see how it works, and then maybe do the 100.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right. Just pause it for now because, like you were saying, the FDA approved means a lot to me.

Speaker 2: The Rougette has, like, three things in it, they say, you know, the sildenafil, Viagra,

Speaker 1: and then some other thing that's supposed to do your brain or whatever.

Speaker 2: Exactly.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: All right. I'm trying to – let me see if I have the login information for Score.

Speaker 1: I do have it. I don't know my – my username is incumbent. I don't know who has saved it.

Speaker 2: Well, what I can do for you is I'll go ahead and pause it for you on my end,

Speaker 1: and then I can email you a password reset, and then that would help you log in.

Speaker 2: Well, I don't even know my username unless I use my email.

Speaker 1: Yeah. Your username would be KeithOlson111 at gmail.com.

Speaker 2: Yes. That's it.

Speaker 1: So, do you think I should keep you on the line until I get the login?

Speaker 2: Oh, no. It's very straightforward, but let me go ahead and adjust your account here.

Speaker 1: Give me one second.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because I'm trying to look in my contacts where I keep some passwords.

Speaker 1: Let me look in my drive folder.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I probably have it in my drive folder.

Speaker 2: Okay. So, I'm going to send you a password reset email.

Speaker 1: You should see that in your inbox now, okay? From there, you'll be able to log in.

Speaker 2: Yeah. I don't have that password saved for some reason.

Speaker 1: No, yeah. You'll be able to reset it. Yep.

Speaker 2: Yeah?

Speaker 1: You can reset it with what I sent you.

Speaker 2: I will, and then I'll go ahead and save everything.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I see the email.

Speaker 1: So, you're going to pause for now?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. It's paused.

Speaker 1: And then I'll put in my calendar the renewal.

Speaker 2: I'll put in a date there after I get this shipment and review it,

Speaker 1: and then I'll put a note in my calendar to possibly reactivate.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, then.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thanks for your help.

Speaker 2: Of course. Happy to help, sir.

Speaker 1: All right. Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
